body:
I have the following example. I want to implement some SVA functions by using the bind method. However, I find that the generated code implements only the functions associated with u_sub1 and u_sub2 does not.
```verilog
interface ral_bkdr_interface;
    class ral_reg_data;
        task write();
         input [2:0] iA;
         input [31:0] iD;
         u_rw.data[iA] = iD;
        endtask
    endclass
endinterface

module rw();
   reg  [31:0] data [7:0];
endmodule

module sub();
   rw u_rw();
endmodule

module top ();
   sub u_sub1();
   sub u_sub2();
   initial begin
      $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
      $finish;
   end
endmodule

bind sub ral_bkdr_interface bkdr_if();
```
The implementation of the wirte task on u_sub2 cannot be found. However, the implementation of the wirte task on u_sub1 can be found.
```cpp
void Vtop_ral_bkdr_interface__03a__03aral_reg_data::__VnoInFunc_write(Vtop__Syms* __restrict vlSymsp, CData/*2:0*/ iA, IData/*31:0*/ iD) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+            Vtop_ral_bkdr_interface__03a__03aral_reg_data::__VnoInFunc_write\n"); );
    // Body
    vlSymsp->TOP.top__DOT__u_sub1__DOT__u_rw__DOT__data[iA] 
        = iD;
}
```
Is there any way that it can take effect in all instances?
